{"id": "duc04-testb-23:7#21", "contents": "Latin American leaders gathered in Portugal for a weekend summit to discuss ways to protect their economies from the global financial crisis. The crisis has led to recession in many countries, threatening the developing economies of Latin America. Cuban President Fidel Castro, an early arrival, described the turmoil in world financial markets as the most pressing issue facing the world. He noted that President Clinton was aware of the potential consequences of a crisis in South America, which could extend to the United States due to its significant investments and loans in the region."}
